Monitoring.name: Outlier Detection
Monitoring.des: An outlier represents the data points which are not in the normal range as specified by threshold values. Any datapoint outside the threshold values will be highlighted as outlier / anomalies. We have given an overall scatter plot for the entire production dataset after reducing the data’s dimensionality if required. Apart from this, we have also given two plots for each feature. One of them is a Probability Density Plot and the other one is a Box Plot. These plots represent outliers with respect to the reference and production data.
